  26 def _get_parsed_url(url):
  27     # type: (S) -> Url
  28     """This is a stand-in function for `urllib3.util.parse_url`
  29 
  30     The orignal function doesn't handle special characters very well, this simply splits
  31     out the authentication section, creates the parsed url, then puts the authentication
  32     section back in, bypassing validation.
  33 
  34     :return: The new, parsed URL object
  35     :rtype: :class:`~urllib3.util.url.Url`
  36     """
  37 
  38     try:
  39         parsed = urllib3_parse(url)
  40     except ValueError:
  41         scheme, _, url = url.partition("://")
  42         auth, _, url = url.rpartition("@")
  43         url = "{scheme}://{url}".format(scheme=scheme, url=url)
  44         parsed = urllib3_parse(url)._replace(auth=auth)
  45     if parsed.auth:
  46         return parsed._replace(auth=url_unquote(parsed.auth))
  47     return parsed

  50 def remove_password_from_url(url):
  51     # type: (S) -> S
  52     """Given a url, remove the password and insert 4 dashes.
  53 
  54     :param url: The url to replace the authentication in
  55     :type url: S
  56     :return: The new URL without authentication
  57     :rtype: S
  58     """
  59 
  60     parsed = _get_parsed_url(url)
  61     if parsed.auth:
  62         auth, _, _ = parsed.auth.partition(":")
  63         return parsed._replace(auth="{auth}:----".format(auth=auth)).url
  64     return parsed.url

  67 @attr.s(hash=True)
  68 class URI(object):
  69     #: The target hostname, e.g. `amazon.com`
  70     host = attr.ib(type=str)
  71     #: The URI Scheme, e.g. `salesforce`
  72     scheme = attr.ib(default="https", type=str)
  73     #: The numeric port of the url if specified
  74     port = attr.ib(default=None, type=int)
  75     #: The url path, e.g. `/path/to/endpoint`
  76     path = attr.ib(default="", type=str)
  77     #: Query parameters, e.g. `?variable=value...`
  78     query = attr.ib(default="", type=str)
  79     #: URL Fragments, e.g. `#fragment=value`
  80     fragment = attr.ib(default="", type=str)
  81     #: Subdirectory fragment, e.g. `&subdirectory=blah...`
  82     subdirectory = attr.ib(default="", type=str)
  83     #: VCS ref this URI points at, if available
  84     ref = attr.ib(default="", type=str)
  85     #: The username if provided, parsed from `user:password@hostname`
  86     username = attr.ib(default="", type=str)
  87     #: Password parsed from `user:password@hostname`
  88     password = attr.ib(default="", type=str, repr=False)
  89     #: An orderedmultidict representing query fragments
  90     query_dict = attr.ib(factory=omdict, type=omdict)
  91     #: The name of the specified package in case it is a VCS URI with an egg fragment
  92     name = attr.ib(default="", type=str)
  93     #: Any extras requested from the requirement
  94     extras = attr.ib(factory=tuple, type=tuple)
  95     #: Whether the url was parsed as a direct pep508-style URL
  96     is_direct_url = attr.ib(default=False, type=bool)
  97     #: Whether the url was an implicit `git+ssh` url (passed as `git+git@`)
  98     is_implicit_ssh = attr.ib(default=False, type=bool)
  99     _auth = attr.ib(default=None, type=str, repr=False)
 100     _fragment_dict = attr.ib(factory=dict, type=dict)
 101     _username_is_quoted = attr.ib(type=bool, default=False)
 102     _password_is_quoted = attr.ib(type=bool, default=False)

 104     def _parse_query(self):
 105         # type: () -> URI
 106         query = self.query if self.query is not None else ""
 107         query_dict = omdict()
 108         queries = query.split("&")
 109         query_items = []
 110         subdirectory = self.subdirectory if self.subdirectory else None
 111         for q in queries:
 112             key, _, val = q.partition("=")
 113             val = unquote_plus(val)
 114             if key == "subdirectory" and not subdirectory:
 115                 subdirectory = val
 116             else:
 117                 query_items.append((key, val))
 118         query_dict.load(query_items)
 119         return attr.evolve(
 120             self, query_dict=query_dict, subdirectory=subdirectory, query=query
 121         )
 122 
 123     def _parse_fragment(self):
 124         # type: () -> URI
 125         subdirectory = self.subdirectory if self.subdirectory else ""
 126         fragment = self.fragment if self.fragment else ""
 127         if self.fragment is None:
 128             return self
 129         fragments = self.fragment.split("&")
 130         fragment_items = {}
 131         name = self.name if self.name else ""
 132         extras = self.extras
 133         for q in fragments:
 134             key, _, val = q.partition("=")
 135             val = unquote_plus(val)
 136             fragment_items[key] = val
 137             if key == "egg":
 138                 from .utils import parse_extras
 139 
 140                 name, stripped_extras = pip_shims.shims._strip_extras(val)
 141                 if stripped_extras:
 142                     extras = tuple(parse_extras(stripped_extras))
 143             elif key == "subdirectory":
 144                 subdirectory = val
 145         return attr.evolve(
 146             self,
 147             fragment_dict=fragment_items,
 148             subdirectory=subdirectory,
 149             fragment=fragment,
 150             extras=extras,
 151             name=name,
 152         )
 153 
 154     def _parse_auth(self):
 155         # type: () -> URI
 156         if self._auth:
 157             username, _, password = self._auth.partition(":")
 158             username_is_quoted, password_is_quoted = False, False
 159             quoted_username, quoted_password = "", ""
 160             if password:
 161                 quoted_password = quote(password)
 162                 password_is_quoted = quoted_password != password
 163             if username:
 164                 quoted_username = quote(username)
 165                 username_is_quoted = quoted_username != username
 166             return attr.evolve(
 167                 self,
 168                 username=quoted_username,
 169                 password=quoted_password,
 170                 username_is_quoted=username_is_quoted,
 171                 password_is_quoted=password_is_quoted,
 172             )
 173         return self
 174 
 175     def get_password(self, unquote=False, include_token=True):
 176         # type: (bool, bool) -> str
 177         password = self.password if self.password else ""
 178         if password and unquote and self._password_is_quoted:
 179             password = url_unquote(password)
 180         return password
 181 
 182     def get_username(self, unquote=False):
 183         # type: (bool) -> str
 184         username = self.username if self.username else ""
 185         if username and unquote and self._username_is_quoted:
 186             username = url_unquote(username)
 187         return username

 189     @staticmethod
 190     def parse_subdirectory(url_part):
 191         # type: (str) -> Tuple[str, Optional[str]]
 192         subdir = None
 193         if "&subdirectory" in url_part:
 194             url_part, _, subdir = url_part.rpartition("&")
 195             if "#egg=" not in url_part:
 196                 subdir = "#{0}".format(subdir.strip())
 197             else:
 198                 subdir = "&{0}".format(subdir.strip())
 199         return url_part.strip(), subdir

 201     @classmethod
 202     def get_parsed_url(cls, url):
 203         # if there is a "#" in the auth section, this could break url parsing
 204         parsed_url = _get_parsed_url(url)
 205         if "@" in url and "#" in url:
 206             scheme = "{0}://".format(parsed_url.scheme)
 207             if parsed_url.scheme == "file":
 208                 scheme = "{0}/".format(scheme)
 209             url_without_scheme = url.replace(scheme, "")
 210             maybe_auth, _, maybe_url = url_without_scheme.partition("@")
 211             if "#" in maybe_auth and (not parsed_url.host or "." not in parsed_url.host):
 212                 new_parsed_url = _get_parsed_url("{0}{1}".format(scheme, maybe_url))
 213                 new_parsed_url = new_parsed_url._replace(auth=maybe_auth)
 214                 return new_parsed_url
 215         return parsed_url

 217     @classmethod
 218     def parse(cls, url):
 219         # type: (S) -> URI
 220         from .utils import DIRECT_URL_RE, split_ref_from_uri
 221 
 222         is_direct_url = False
 223         name_with_extras = None
 224         is_implicit_ssh = url.strip().startswith("git+git@")
 225         if is_implicit_ssh:
 226             from ..utils import add_ssh_scheme_to_git_uri
 227 
 228             url = add_ssh_scheme_to_git_uri(url)
 229         direct_match = DIRECT_URL_RE.match(url)
 230         if direct_match is not None:
 231             is_direct_url = True
 232             name_with_extras, _, url = url.partition("@")
 233             name_with_extras = name_with_extras.strip()
 234         url, ref = split_ref_from_uri(url.strip())
 235         if "file:/" in url and "file:///" not in url:
 236             url = url.replace("file:/", "file:///")
 237         parsed = cls.get_parsed_url(url)
 238         # if there is a "#" in the auth section, this could break url parsing
 239         if not (parsed.scheme and parsed.host):
 240             # check if this is a file uri
 241             if not (
 242                 parsed.scheme
 243                 and parsed.path
 244                 and (parsed.scheme == "file" or parsed.scheme.endswith("+file"))
 245             ):
 246                 raise ValueError("Failed parsing URL {0!r} - Not a valid url".format(url))
 247         parsed_dict = dict(parsed._asdict()).copy()
 248         parsed_dict["is_direct_url"] = is_direct_url
 249         parsed_dict["is_implicit_ssh"] = is_implicit_ssh
 250         parsed_dict.update(
 251             **update_url_name_and_fragment(name_with_extras, ref, parsed_dict)
 252         )  # type: ignore
 253         return cls(**parsed_dict)._parse_auth()._parse_query()._parse_fragment()
 254 
 255     def to_string(
 256         self,
 257         escape_password=True,  # type: bool
 258         unquote=True,  # type: bool
 259         direct=None,  # type: Optional[bool]
 260         strip_ssh=False,  # type: bool
 261         strip_ref=False,  # type: bool
 262         strip_name=False,  # type: bool
 263         strip_subdir=False,  # type: bool
 264     ):
 265         # type: (...) -> str
 266         """Converts the current URI to a string, unquoting or escaping the
 267         password as needed.
 268 
 269         :param escape_password: Whether to replace password with ``----``, default True
 270         :param escape_password: bool, optional
 271         :param unquote: Whether to unquote url-escapes in the password, default False
 272         :param unquote: bool, optional
 273         :param bool direct: Whether to format as a direct URL
 274         :param bool strip_ssh: Whether to strip the SSH scheme from the url (git only)
 275         :param bool strip_ref: Whether to drop the VCS ref (if present)
 276         :param bool strip_name: Whether to drop the name and extras (if present)
 277         :param bool strip_subdir: Whether to drop the subdirectory (if present)
 278         :return: The reconstructed string representing the URI
 279         :rtype: str
 280         """
 281 
 282         if direct is None:
 283             direct = self.is_direct_url
 284         if escape_password:
 285             password = "----" if self.password else ""
 286             if password:
 287                 username = self.get_username(unquote=unquote)
 288             elif self.username:
 289                 username = "----"
 290             else:
 291                 username = ""
 292         else:
 293             password = self.get_password(unquote=unquote)
 294             username = self.get_username(unquote=unquote)
 295         auth = ""
 296         if username:
 297             if password:
 298                 auth = "{username}:{password}@".format(
 299                     password=password, username=username
 300                 )
 301             else:
 302                 auth = "{username}@".format(username=username)
 303         query = ""
 304         if self.query:
 305             query = "{query}?{self.query}".format(query=query, self=self)
 306         subdir_prefix = "#"
 307         if not direct:
 308             if self.name and not strip_name:
 309                 fragment = "#egg={self.name_with_extras}".format(self=self)
 310                 subdir_prefix = "&"
 311             elif not strip_name and (
 312                 self.extras and self.scheme and self.scheme.startswith("file")
 313             ):
 314                 from .utils import extras_to_string
 315 
 316                 fragment = extras_to_string(self.extras)
 317             else:
 318                 fragment = ""
 319             query = "{query}{fragment}".format(query=query, fragment=fragment)
 320         if self.subdirectory and not strip_subdir:
 321             query = "{query}{subdir_prefix}subdirectory={self.subdirectory}".format(
 322                 query=query, subdir_prefix=subdir_prefix, self=self
 323             )
 324         host_port_path = self.get_host_port_path(strip_ref=strip_ref)
 325         url = "{self.scheme}://{auth}{host_port_path}{query}".format(
 326             self=self, auth=auth, host_port_path=host_port_path, query=query
 327         )
 328         if strip_ssh:
 329             from ..utils import strip_ssh_from_git_uri
 330 
 331             url = strip_ssh_from_git_uri(url)
 332         if self.name and direct and not strip_name:
 333             return "{self.name_with_extras}@ {url}".format(self=self, url=url)
 334         return url
 335 
 336     def get_host_port_path(self, strip_ref=False):
 337         # type: (bool) -> str
 338         host = self.host if self.host else ""
 339         if self.port is not None:
 340             host = "{host}:{self.port!s}".format(host=host, self=self)
 341         path = "{self.path}".format(self=self) if self.path else ""
 342         if self.ref and not strip_ref:
 343             path = "{path}@{self.ref}".format(path=path, self=self)
 344         return "{host}{path}".format(host=host, path=path)

 346     @property
 347     def hidden_auth(self):
 348         # type: () -> str
 349         auth = ""
 350         if self.username and self.password:
 351             password = "****"
 352             username = self.get_username(unquote=True)
 353             auth = "{username}:{password}".format(username=username, password=password)
 354         elif self.username and not self.password:
 355             auth = "****"
 356         return auth

 358     @property
 359     def name_with_extras(self):
 360         # type: () -> str
 361         from .utils import extras_to_string
 362 
 363         if not self.name:
 364             return ""
 365         extras = extras_to_string(self.extras)
 366         return "{self.name}{extras}".format(self=self, extras=extras)

 476 def update_url_name_and_fragment(name_with_extras, ref, parsed_dict):
 477     # type: (Optional[str], Optional[str], Dict[str, Optional[str]]) -> Dict[str, Optional[str]]
 478     if name_with_extras:
 479         fragment = ""  # type: Optional[str]
 480         parsed_extras = ()
 481         name, extras = pip_shims.shims._strip_extras(name_with_extras)
 482         if extras:
 483             parsed_extras = parsed_extras + tuple(parse_extras(extras))
 484         if parsed_dict["fragment"] is not None:
 485             fragment = "{0}".format(parsed_dict["fragment"])
 486             if fragment.startswith("egg="):
 487                 _, _, fragment_part = fragment.partition("=")
 488                 fragment_name, fragment_extras = pip_shims.shims._strip_extras(
 489                     fragment_part
 490                 )
 491                 name = name if name else fragment_name
 492                 if fragment_extras:
 493                     parsed_extras = parsed_extras + tuple(parse_extras(fragment_extras))
 494                 name_with_extras = "{0}{1}".format(name, extras_to_string(parsed_extras))
 495         elif (
 496             parsed_dict.get("path") is not None and "&subdirectory" in parsed_dict["path"]
 497         ):
 498             path, fragment = URI.parse_subdirectory(parsed_dict["path"])  # type: ignore
 499             parsed_dict["path"] = path
 500         elif ref is not None and "&subdirectory" in ref:
 501             ref, fragment = URI.parse_subdirectory(ref)
 502         parsed_dict["name"] = name
 503         parsed_dict["extras"] = parsed_extras
 504     if ref:
 505         parsed_dict["ref"] = ref.strip()
 506     return parsed_dict
